  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Not Accepted — marginal shortfall)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment completed. Two factors (Discretization error and Model form) achieved levels marginally below their required thresholds. The assessment team reviewed the evidence and concluded that the shortfalls, while small in absolute terms, cannot be resolved by compensating evidence from other factors at MRL 2, and the decision is therefore Not accepted pending remediation.",
