      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/sqa-mrl2",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023R2) is used under a documented software quality plan that includes version control, regression testing, and a formal release process. All simulation scripts are archived in a version-controlled repository with change logs. Achieved level 2 meets the required level 2 for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/code-verification-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy tests were performed on canonical rotating-flow benchmarks included in the solver's verification suite. Results confirm second-order spatial accuracy for the velocity and pressure fields. Achieved level 2 meets the required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/discretization-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "A three-mesh Richardson extrapolation study was conducted (coarse 4.2 M, medium 9.8 M, fine 21.4 M cells). The grid convergence index (GCI) for the hemolysis index QoI is 6.8% on the medium mesh selected for production runs, exceeding the 5% threshold established in the acceptance criteria for level 3. The study demonstrates asymptotic convergence (GCI ratio 1.02) and the error is systematic and bounded, but the magnitude places the evidence at level 2 rather than the required level 3. This shortfall is documented and was not resolved by the fine-mesh sensitivity runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/test-conditions-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Experimental validation tests were conducted at the same five flow-speed operating points used in the simulation study. Fluid temperature, hematocrit (35%), and anticoagulant protocol were controlled and documented. Pump geometry was measured post-test to confirm dimensional conformance within 0.05 mm. Achieved level 3 exceeds the required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/output-comparison-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against measured values at all five operating points. Mean absolute error is 8.2% with all predictions within the combined experimental and simulation uncertainty bands. A formal uncertainty budget was constructed per ASME V&V 20. Achieved level 3 exceeds the required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate). This quantity is directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1) and is the quantity computed in both simulation and experiment. Achieved level 2 meets the required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were performed on the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under CPB-representative flow rates (2–6 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM). The validation domain overlaps the intended COU operating envelope. Achieved level 2 meets the required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/solver-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 with medium model influence, a detailed iterative-solver error analysis beyond residual monitoring is not required per the ASME V&V 40 factor matrix. Residual convergence to 1e-6 for all equations was confirmed for every simulation run. Scoped out with documented justification; requiredLevel 1 is satisfied by residual monitoring alone."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/use-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, formal use-error analysis beyond documented simulation protocols is not required. All simulations were executed by trained analysts following a documented simulation execution plan (SEP-CPB-2025). Independent review of boundary condition setup was conducted. Scoped out with documented justification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/model-form-mrl2",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on its established performance for rotating internal flows. A comparative study against the realizable k-epsilon model showed differences of up to 12% in peak shear stress regions near the impeller blade tips, which are the dominant contributors to the hemolysis index. The acceptance criterion for level 3 requires that model-form uncertainty be bounded to within 10% for the primary QoI via multi-model comparison or physics-based justification. The observed 12% spread marginally exceeds this threshold, placing the evidence at level 2. The team evaluated whether the conservative nature of SST (higher shear stress predictions) could serve as a compensating argument, but concluded that the 2-percentage-point exceedance is not resolvable by qualitative reasoning alone and requires either an additional turbulence model comparison or experimental near-wall velocity data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/model-inputs-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity was modeled using the Carreau-Yasuda non-Newtonian model with parameters derived from published rheological data at 35% hematocrit. Pump geometry was imported from CAD files with dimensional verification. Inlet boundary conditions (flow rate, velocity profile) were derived from the experimental test rig measurements. Achieved level 2 meets the required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/test-samples-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Three nominally identical pump units were tested across the five operating points, with three repeat runs per operating point per unit (n=45 total measurements). Inter-unit variability was characterized and incorporated into the uncertainty budget. Achieved level 2 meets the required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/input-equivalency-mrl2",
      "rationale": "The simulation input parameters (flow rates, rotational speeds, fluid properties, geometric dimensions) were mapped to the experimental test conditions through a formal equivalency matrix. Deviations between nominal simulation inputs and measured experimental conditions were quantified and found to be within 2% for all parameters. Achieved level 2 meets the required level 2."
    }
